The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Wednesday, December 08, 2004 

 Security slot in police shuffle 

 A STAFF REPORTER 

 Calcutta, Dec. 7: The government today shuffled the top police brass by transferring or promoting 39 IPS and 12 state police officers. 

 It also created a post of deputy commissioner (security) to take charge of security arrangements for important persons in Calcutta. Pankaj Dutta, special superintendent of the Intelligence Branch, got the post. 

 Partha Bhattacharya, additional commissioner, has been posted as inspector-general (railways). He will be replaced by Anil Kumar, IG (police training). Jit Ram Bhagat, IG (railways), has been promoted as additional director-general (railways). 

 Ranveer Kumar, deputy commissioner (eastern suburban division), will take charge as DC (headquarters). He will be replaced by Jawed Shamim, DC of the 1st battalion of Calcutta Armed Police (CAP). 

 Murshidabad superintendent Gyanwant Singh was appointed DC (central) in place of Rajeev Kumar, who has been promoted as deputy IG (operations) in the CID. Sanjoy Singh, DC of the 3rd battalion of CAP, will replace Gyanwant Singh. 

 A.M. Ranade, DC of the CAP?s 4th battalion, will take charge as DC (port). 

 G.A. Srinivas, additional Malda superintendent, has been promoted as DC of 1st battalion of CAP. 




